  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd3\u0dba \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dbb \u0dc0\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dca \u0da7\u0ddc\u0db1\u0dca 15000 \u0d9a\u0dca \u0dad\u0dda \u0dc0\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "15000 metric tons of Indian fertilizers for tea cultivation",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Conservation Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera said that it was decided to provide 15,000 metric tons of urea fertilizer received from India for tea cultivation.",
        "Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera went to the Ministry of Agriculture after taking oath as the Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources of the new government and discussed the distribution of urea fertilizer and the fuel requirements.",
        "According to the Ministry of Agriculture, 65,000 metric tons of urea fertilizer received under the Indian loan scheme is to be received and so far 44,000 metric tons of fertilizer has been received.",
        "The presidents of the two government-owned fertilizer companies informed the minister that nearly 60 percent of the urea stock has been distributed.",
        "The minister instructed to produce a special mixed fertilizer needed for vegetable cultivation very quickly and arrange to supply that fertilizer to the market within the next two weeks.",
        "Speaking to the media, the Minister of Agriculture said that he is also of the position that the new president should be given reasonable time to work."
      ],
